TY  - JOUR
AU  - Akerlof, George A.
AU  - Yellen, Janet L.
T1  - The Fair Wage-Effort Hypothesis and Unemployment*
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/2937787
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 105
IS  - 2
SP  - 255
EP  - 283
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper introduces the fair wage-effort hypothesis and explores its implications. This hypothesis is motivated by equity theory in social psychology and social exchange theory in sociology. According to the fair wage-effort hypothesis, workers proportionately withdraw effort as their actual wage falls short of their fair wage. Such behavior causes unemployment and is also consistent with observed cross-section wage differentials and unemployment patterns.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2937787
ER  - 



