TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bruno, Michael
AU  - Fischer, Stanley
T1  - Seigniorage, Operating Rules, and the High Inflation Trap*
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/05/01
DO  - 10.2307/2937791
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 105
IS  - 2
SP  - 353
EP  - 374
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - There may be both a high and a low inflation equilibrium when the government finances the deficit through seigniorage. Under rational expectations the high inflation equilibrium is stable, and the low inflation equilibrium unstable; under adaptive expectations or lagged adjustment of money balances with rational expectations, the low inflation equilibrium may be stable. Adding bond financing, dual equilibria remain if the government fixes the real interest rate, but a unique equilibrium is attained when the government sets a nominal anchor for the economy. The existence of dual equilibria is thus a result of the government's operating rules.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2937791
ER  - 



